-- Pioneer Food Group Approaches KWV About Buying South African Wine Company
-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 2010-10-29T15:31:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-29/pioneer-food-group-says-it-approached-kwv-holdings-about-buying-company.html
Pioneer Food Group Ltd. , the South
African maker of Sasko bread and Weet-Bix cereal, said it
approached  KWV Holdings Ltd.  about buying South Africa’s second-
largest wine and spirits company.  “There can be no certainty that these discussions will
lead to a transaction,” the company said in a statement today.  Pioneer was unchanged at 49.01 rand by the 5 p.m. close of
Johannesburg trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Franz Wild  in Johannesburg at 
 fwild@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter Hirschberg in Jerusalem at 
 phirschberg@bloomberg.net . 